---
title: Yakitori-Style Steak Skewers with Soy Butter Broccoli & Mushrooms over Toasted Sesame Rice
description: At Japanese-tapas style pubs, yakitori is standard fare. Literally translating to “grilled bird,” this dish is typically made with chicken—but this time, our chefs are raising the steaks. (See what we did there?) This deluxe adaptation swaps in bite-size steak cooked with bell peppers and scallions and glazed in a savory-sweet sauce. Skewers are served over a bed of sesame rice and roasted bell pepper, broccoli, and mushrooms tossed in a soy butter sauce.
